fMqhlNhLxlD0AyjMGXu4bVOiwuYf9c=\",\"summary\":[{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Evaluating environment variables**\\n\\nI'm working through the changelog that discusses the behavior of environment variables. It seems like I might need to set up these variables to test a new feature, though the user prefers \\\"no action\\\" unless specific setup is necessary. I’m thinking some guidance might help, especially if the environment setup could lead to nondeterministic tests. I should explore documentation more about the default builder and how it handles these cases. I also wonder if my understanding of the setup is complete here.\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Considering test setup guidance**\\n\\nI’m thinking about how tests could become flaky due to CI environments. Existing tests use an empty builder with explicit decoders to avoid this. The agent guidance might state that no environment is required and suggest using MapPropertySource or PropsPropertySource instead. I wonder if including test setup guidance would be beneficial, even if it’s marked as no action. Providing advice on using built-in properties instead of YAML could simplify things, especially since YAML requires an optional dependency. I may need to dive into the Javadocs to get a clearer understanding.\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Assessing dependency risks**\\n\\nI'm considering the risks if the agent follows the documentation and uses YAML or JSON, which would require adding extra dependencies. I’ll need to check the existing generated metadata since the new version uses Kotlin 2.1 while the previous one was on Kotlin 1.7.10. I wonder if the driver will update the dependency versions on its own. I could run a command like `jar tf | grep META-INF/services` to see the service loader. That might provide clarity on the setup.\"}]}"}, {"type": "toolCall", "id": "call_h4IqhW8rmb7VWSWEP40oi3dx|fc_0106925b7376a3df016a41031e88d48193bd5cbff5fac0782a", "name": "bash", "arguments